DataTypes:

1.Numeric: 
INT, SMALLINT, FLOAT, REAL, DOUBLE PRECISION, DECIMAL(i,j)

2.Character-String:
CHAR(n), VARCHAR(n), CLOB

3.Bit-String:
BIT(n), BITVARYING(n)

4.Boolean:
TRUE, FALSE, UNKNOWN

5.Date&Time:
DATE yyyy-mm-dd, TIME hh:mm:ss

6.Timestamp


***CONSTRAINTS***
Constraints in simple terms are the rules that can beapplied on the type of data in a table.

1.NOT NULL: Ensures that a Null value cannot be stored in a column.

2.UNIQUE: This constraint makes sure that all the values in a 
column are different.

3.CHECK: This constraint ensures that all the values in a column satisfy a
specific condition.

4.DEFAULT: This constraint considts of a set of defalut values for a 
column when no values is specified.

5.INDEX: This constraint is used to create and retrieve data from the 
database very quickly.
